          "headline": "Piastri's Cruel DNS",
          "body": "Oscar Piastri crashed at Turn 4 on the sighting lap — before the race had started — becoming only the fourth driver in F1 history to retire before reaching the grid. At his home race, in front of his home crowd, with McLaren having what looked like a legitimate top-5 car. He scored zero points while team-mate Norris scored 10. The championship deficit after Round 1 had nothing to do with racing."
        }
